3.230. 
Property whose legal regime is determined by the provisions of this Chapter 
1. The rules of this Chapter shall determine the legal regime of the property provided for in this Article if the cohabitants have jointly acquired and jointly use that property. 
2. The following property shall be regarded as jointly used by the cohabitants:
1) a dwelling-house or flat acquired jointly and used by the cohabitants in their cohabitation; 
2) a lease, usufruct or other right of one of the spouses to use a dwelling-house or flat used by the cohabitants in their cohabitation;
3) immovable property acquired jointly in connection with a dwelling-house or apartment used for cohabitation, provided that the immovable property is used jointly by the cohabitants; 
4) furniture and other household effects acquired and used jointly by the cohabitants, other than those used by the cohabitants in their individual capacity.
3. The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to property used by the cohabitants for recreational purposes (garden, summer house, etc.).
